ve a full kitchen with stove, fridge, microwave, toaster, coffee maker, so you'll save money by stocking up and having breakfast at &quot;home&quot; every morning.Several restaurants and bars nearby. The small indian place attached to the building downstairs (forgot the name) was very good.A few complaints:- For such a large place that can accomodate 4+ guests, the closet space was limited and (this is my pet peeve about most hotel rooms) not a single wall/door hook in the entire unit. Not even in the bathroom. So, no place to hang your jackets, hats, bathrobes, wet clothes, etc.- The temperature dial in one of the showers was broken (ranged from hot to scalding, not cold to hot) and after three repair-requests at the front desk we were finally told that they were just concierges and we had to talk to the office manager. Went to the office and was informed (a bit late) that room problems should not be reported to the front desk, and that the maintenance man was not working that day (Saturday), but they'd fix it tomorrow. Never happened. Good thing we had a second shower! So...if you have a problem with the room, don't bother with the front desk.- We had also asked for a second key from the front desk. That request was apparently ignored for three days, until my visit to the office, where they gave me the key right away.- Stepping out of the high &amp; slippery bathtup was a bit dangerous because the only thing to hold onto is the heated towel rack (ouch), or the loose, half-tub-door. So, be careful.- A room safe would've been nice.Overall, if you're looking for a lot of bang-for-your-buck with regard to space and location, and your comfort does not depend on typical hotel amenities, this is an excellent choice.	
