Jan 11 2008 	Amazing experience	I stayed there early Jan and booked a '1 bedroom premier' direct from the marlinapartments.com web site. Always do this - it's much cheaper than laterooms.com or other offers and they have a price guarantee.Before, my experience of London hotels was a small-ish room en suite which can easily cost up to £80-90 if you don't reserve it early.The marlin apartments are very easy to find - it's the stunning building opposite the Borough tube station. The concierge is quick and efficient and you get a key fob to the main apartment entry + a key for the room. You will need ID for check-in which could have been a pain but I always carry some.The apartment was absolutely stunning. There is:- a bathroom with a good strong shower and molton brown toiletries.- an open plan kitchen with dishwasher, washing machine, microwave, oven + hood, fridge-freezer- open plan dining area and lounge with LCD tv, satellite (no movies / sports) and DVD player.- a bedroom with fitted wardrobesThe whole place is spotless and beautifully cleaned. If you are arriving late, there is a complimentary set of snacks including crisps, chocolate, nuti-grain bar, cereal for one, cup-a-soup and a pasta snack as well and tea &amp; coffee. You get lots of cutlery, a toaster, a kettle, a coffee filter (filter coffee not supplied).The windows are floor to ceiling in the main room and the views from 6th floor up are stunning as the apartments are higher than surrounding place at this point.Overall a stunning luxury experience at London prices.	
